explains: adj. 不自然的；反常的；不近人情的
wordGroup: unnatural death 非自然死，恶死

sentences.en: Her leg was bent at an unnatural angle.
sentences.cn: 她的腿弯曲的角度反常。

sentences.en: There was an unnatural silence and then a scream.
sentences.cn: 一阵反常的寂静，接着便是一声尖叫。

sentences.en: It seems unnatural for a child to spend so much time alone.
sentences.cn: 一个孩子独自一人待那么长时间似乎有点反常。
